Date:  0/0/1853
Source:  Adventures of a Surveyor
Author:  ROCHFORT
Vol / Page:  22
Edition:
Quote:  The house was what is called a toi-toi whare; the toi-toi is a reed which the natives use for the walls and roofs of their huts; these reeds are plaited together with flax; ... The New Zealanders will build a house in this manner for a white man for five pounds. [fn] Whare is the native name for house.
